SIMPLE: sluttish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sluttish
<hw>Slut"tish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Like a slut; untidy;
indecently negligent of cleanliness; disorderly; <as>as, a
<ex>sluttish</ex> woman</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why is thy lord so <qex>slutish</qex>, I thee pray.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An air of liberal, though <qex>sluttish</qex>, plenty, indicated
the wealthy farmer.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Slut"tish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Slut"tish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sly</ent>⟦br⟧
